main event: An observer photographed a bright circular object in the sky at Ft. Stockton, Texas on March 26, 1952.
interesting points: The observation occurred at approximately 7:15 P.M.,The object was described as bright and circular against a dark background,There is a clock or dial visible in the image, with the text 'Circ' below it, The photograph taken is one of several captured during the observation, The object was moving across the sky when it was photographed.
sighted object: a bright circular object in the sky
